				<h3 id="post-3310"><a href="http://samablog.robsama.com/?p=3310" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to What Cramer Meant">What Cramer Meant</a></h3>
				<small>Wednesday, March 19th, 2008</small>

				<div class="entry">
					<p>So there seems to be some confusion about what Jim Cramer meant when he said it would be ridiculous to pull your money out of Bear Stearns.  Did he mean that Bear Stearns was a stock that you shouldn&#8217;t dump, or that your money would be safe in Bear Stearns investment accounts.  He claims the latter.  Don Harrold begs to differ:</p>
<p><center><object width="425" height="355"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/772PXNSrSiI&#038;hl=en"></param><param name="wmode" value="transparent"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/772PXNSrSiI&#038;hl=en" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" width="425" height="355"></embed></object></center></p>
				</div>

				<p class="postmetadata">Tags: <a href="http://samablog.robsama.com/?tag=bear-stearns" rel="tag">Bear Stearns</a>, <a href="http://samablog.robsama.com/?tag=don-harrold" rel="tag">Don Harrold</a>, <a href="http://samablog.robsama.com/?tag=jim-cramer" rel="tag">Jim Cramer</a><br /> Posted in <a href="http://samablog.robsama.com/?cat=4" title="View all posts in News &amp; Politics" rel="category">News & Politics</a> |   <a href="http://samablog.robsama.com/?p=3310#respond" title="Comment on What Cramer Meant">No Comments &#187;</a></p>

